s)|Top Gear]]''\n|Himself (guest)\n|1 episode\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Web Therapy|Web Therapy]]''\n|rowspan=2|Nick Jericho\n|Web series; 3 episodes\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Web Therapy (TV series)]]''\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|2015\n|''The Prince''\n|\n|Television movie, producer\n|-\n|2016\u20132019\n|''[[Top Gear (2002 TV series)|Top Gear]]''\n|Himself (host)\n|24 episodes (series [[Top Gear (series 23)|23]], [[Top Gear (series 24)|24]], [[Top Gear (series 25)|25]], [[Top Gear (series 26)|26]])\n|-\n|2016\u2013present\n|''[[Man with a Plan (TV series)|Man with a Plan]]''\n|Adam Burns\n|Lead; 56 episodes, executive producer\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Friends|The One Where They Got Back Together]]''\n| Himself\n| [[HBO Max]] special; also executive producer<ref>{{cite web |last1=Andreeva |first1=Nellie |last2=Petski |first2=Denise |title=\u2018Friends\u2019 Reunion Special Officially A Go At HBO Max With Cast Returning |url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/friends-reunion-special-confirmed-hbo-max-cast-returning-jennifer-aniston-courtney-cox-1202865593 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=February 24, 2020 |language=en |date=February 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Individual awards\n!Year\n!Association\n!Award\n!Nominated work\n!Role\n!Result\n|-\n|2000\n|[[American Comedy Awards]]\n|Funniest Supporting Male Performer in a Television Series\n| rowspan=\"13\" |''[[Friends]]''\n| rowspan=\"15\" |[[Joey Tribbiani]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2002\n|[[Prime|Primetime Emmy Awards]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Lead Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|[[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|Favorite Television Actor\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|[[TCA Awards|Television Critics Association Awards]]\n|Outstanding Individual Achievement in Comedy\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|[[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|Choice TV Actor - Comedy\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2003\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award|Primetime Emmy Awards]]\