{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* {{IMDb name|1455}}\n* [http://www.emmys.com/celebrities/matt-leblanc Matt LeBlanc] at [[Emmys.com]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes person|matt_leblanc}}\n* {{TV Guide person|165294}}\n* {{twitter|Matt_LeBlanc}}\n{{div end}}\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Awards for Matt LeBlanc\n|list={{Golden Globe Award Best Actor TV Comedy}}\n{{People's Choice Award for Favorite Actor in a New TV Series}}{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVComedy 1994\u20131999}}}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leblanc, Matt}}\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:Actors from Newton, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American people of French-Canadian descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Best Musical or Comedy Actor Golden Globe (television) winners]]\n[[Category:Comedians from California]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Newton North High School alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Hidden Hills, California]]\n[[Category:Top Gear people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Matt LeBlanc\n| image              = X 217c5312.jpg\n| caption            = LeBlanc in 2011\n| birth_name         = Matthew Steven LeBlanc\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1967|07|25}}\n| birth_place        = [[Newton, Massachusetts]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actor, comedian\n| years_active       = 1987\u2013present\n| net_worth          = $80 million<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.insider.com/cast-of-friends-ranked-by-net-worth-2018-9 |title=How much the cast of 'Friends' is estimated to be worth today |first=Nicole |last=Pomarico |date=September 21, 2018 |publisher=[[Insider Inc|Insider]] }}</ref>\n| known_for          = ''[[Friends]]'', [[Episodes (TV series)|''Episodes'']], [[Man with a Plan (TV series)|''Man with a Plan'']], [[Joey (TV series)|''Joey'']], [[Top Gear (2002 TV series)|''Top Gear'']]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Melissa McKnight|2003|2006|reason=divorced}}\n| partner            = {{ubl|[[Andrea Anders]] (2006\u20132015)|Aurora Mulligan (2016\u2013present)}}\n| children           = 1<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cF45SRk-DCE?t=472|title=Matt LeBlanc Is Not Afraid To Live on the Wild Side|website=[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]|date=October 22, 2016|accessdate=August 22, 2017|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Matthew Steven LeBlanc''' ({{IPAc-en|l|\u0259|\u02c8|b|l|\u0252|\u014b|k}}; born July 25, 1967) is an American actor and comedian.<ref name=filmref /> He is best known for his portrayal of dim-witted yet well-intentioned womaniser [[Joey Tribbiani]] in the [[NBC]] sitcom ''[[Friends]]'' and in its [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] series ''[[Joey (TV series)|Joey]]''. For his work on ''Friends'', LeBlanc received three [[Emmy Award]] nominations. He has also starred as a fictionalized version of himself in ''[[Episodes (TV series)|Episodes]]'' (2011\u20132017), for which he won a [[Golden Globe Award]] and received four additional Emmy Award nominations. He co-hosted [[Top Gear (2002 TV series)|''Top Gear'']] from 2016 to 2019. {{As of|2016}}, he plays Adam Burns in ''[[Man with a Plan (TV series)|Man with a Plan]]''.\n\n== Early life ==\nLeBlanc was born in [[Newton, Massachusetts]]. His mother, Patricia (n\u00e9e Di Cillo), was an office manager; his father, Paul LeBlanc, was a mechanic.<ref name=\"filmref\">{{cite web |url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/2/Matt-LeBlanc.html |title=Matt LeBlanc (1967\u2013 ) |website=FilmReference.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20140080,00.html |title=Way to Go, Joey! |first=Michelle |last=Tauber |date=May 19, 2003 |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.italoamericano.org/story/2015-10-16/mattleblanc |title=Matt LeBlanc takes his Italian origins to his heart|date=October 16, 2015 |website=Italo-Americano |accessdate=August 22, 2017}}</ref> His father is of French-Canadian descent and his mother is of Italian ancestry.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/10833366/Matt-LeBlanc-I-have-an-ego-but-I-try-to-leave-it-at-the-door.html |title=Matt LeBlanc: 'I have an ego, but I try to leave it at the door' |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |location=London |first=Stephanie |last=Rafanelli |date=May 17, 2014 |accessdate=January 7, 2015 |archivedate=January 7, 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150107231538/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/10833366/Matt-LeBlanc-I-have-an-ego-but-I-try-to-leave-it-at-the-door.html |url-status=live |df= }}</ref> He attended [[Newton North High School]], and graduated in 1985, alongside comedian [[Louis C.K.]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Louis C.K. and Matt LeBlanc, way back when |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/names/2015/09/19/emmy-nominees-louis-and-matt-leblanc-knew-them-when/K8mD1IpH0Fr5HtyZZvGe6L/story.html |first=Jill |last=Radsken |date=September 20, 2015 |newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]] |accessdate=March 28, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news| url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/matt-leblanc-i-was-getting-divorced-work-wasnt-a-priority-it-was-a-rough-time-cmql82nl8| title=Matt LeBlanc: 'I was getting divorced, work wasn't a priority \u2014 it was a rough time' '| last=Rose| first=Hilary|date=March 20, 2018| work=[[The Times]]| location=London| access-date=March 21, 2018| language=en| issn=0140-0460}}</ref> He moved to New York at the age of 17 to pursue a career in modelling.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 1987\u20131994: Early career ===\n[[File:Matt Le Blanc.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|LeBlanc at the [[47th Primetime Emmy Awards]], 1995]]\nLeBlanc first appeared in a 1987 [[Heinz Tomato Ketchup]] commercial. In 1988, he starred in the television drama ''[[TV 101]]'' for one season. In 1991, he had a recurring role on the hit [[Fox (network)|Fox]] sitcom ''[[Married... with Children]]''. He played Vinnie Verducci, the son of one the protagonist's friends and boyfriend to his daughter. He went on to star in two short-lived spin-offs: ''[[Top of the Heap]]'' (1991) and ''[[Vinnie and Bobby]]'' (1992).\n\nHe appeared in two [[Bon Jovi]] music videos: \"[[Miracle (Jon Bon Jovi song)|Miracle]]\", from the ''[[Young Guns II]]'' soundtrack in 1990, and \"[[Say It Isn't So (Bon Jovi song)|Say It Isn't So]]\" in 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GRSB-QZHpXM |title=Bon Jovi \u2013 Say It Isn' So |work=YouTube |accessdate=May 22, 2011}}</ref> He also appeared in videos for [[Alanis Morissette]]'s single \"[[Walk Away (Alanis Morissette song)|Walk Away]]\", [[Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers]]' \"[[Into the Great Wide Open (song)|Into the Great Wide Open]]\", and [[Bob Seger]]'s \"[[Night Moves (song)|Night Moves]]\".<ref name=\"Episode 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01brd8t |title=Top Gear; Series 18, Episode 2 |website=[[BBC Two]] |accessdate=February 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== 1994\u20132004: ''Friends'' ===\nLeBlanc found success in the role of [[Joey Tribbiani]] on ''[[Friends]]'', and went on to play this character for 12 years \u2014 10 seasons of ''Friends'' and two seasons of [[Joey (TV series)|''Joey'']]. ''Friends'' was wildly successful, and LeBlanc, along with his co-stars, gained wide recognition among viewers. This ensemble situation comedy became a major hit for NBC, airing on Thursday nights for ten years.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.notablebiographies.com/newsmakers2/2005-La-Pr/LeBlanc-Matt.html| title=Matt LeBlanc Biography - life, family, children, parents, name, story, wife, school, mother - Newsmakers Cumulation| website=www.notablebiographies.com| language=en| access-date=December 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nFor his performance, LeBlanc received three [[Primetime Emmy Award]] nominations, three [[Golden Globe]] award nominations, and one [[Screen Actors Guild Award]] nomination. During this time he also appeared in the films ''[[Lookin' Italian]]'' (1994), ''[[Ed (film)|Ed]]'' (1996), ''[[Lost in Space (film)|Lost in Space]]'' (1998), ''[[Charlie's Angels (2000 film)|Charlie's Angels]]'' (2000), and its sequel, ''[[Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle]]'' (2003).\n\n=== 2006\u20132011: Hiatus ===\nFollowing the cancellation of ''[[Joey (TV series)|Joey]]'', LeBlanc announced that he would be taking a one-year hiatus from acting on TV, which eventually turned into five years. His next role was a fictionalized version of himself on ''[[Episodes (TV series)|Episodes]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Matt LeBlanc on Life after 'Friends' and Taking a Six Year Hiatus |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/video/matt-leblanc-life-friends-taking-712923 |date=June 27, 2014 |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=March 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== 2011\u2013present: Career revival ===\n[[File:LeBlanc and Meryl at 69th Annual Golden Globes Awards.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|LeBlanc at the Golden Globes with [[Meryl Streep]], 2012]]\nFrom 2011, LeBlanc began appearing as a fictional version of himself in [[Episodes (TV series)|''Episodes'']], a television series about a fictional American remake of an equally fictional British television series.<ref>{{cite news |first=James |last=Rampton |date=January 6, 2011 |title=Episodes: The one where Matt LeBlanc plays himself... |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/features/episodes-the-one-where-matt-leblanc-plays-himself-2177012.html |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |accessdate=March 2, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=January 4, 2011 |title=Matt LeBlanc Spoofs Himself On Comedy 'Episodes' |url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/matt-leblanc-pokes-fun-at-the-world-of-tv-friends-and-himself-on-showtimes-episodes_article_41726 |website=[[Access Hollywood]] |accessdate=March 2, 2011}}</ref> The series is written by ''Friends'' co-creator [[David Crane (producer)|David Crane]] and his partner [[Jeffrey Klarik]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Parks |first=Tim |date=September 30, 2009 |title=LeBlanc to star as himself on 'Episodes' |url= http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/a179903/leblanc-to-star-as-himself-on-episodes.html |website=[[Digital Spy]] |accessdate=September 30, 2009}}</ref> At the [[69th Golden Globe Awards]] in 2012, LeBlanc won the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Television Series Musical or Comedy|Golden Globe Award for Best Actor]] in a television series, musical, or comedy, and was nominated for an additional four [[Primetime Emmy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldenglobes.org/nominations/ |title=Nominations & Winners |website=Golden Globes |accessdate=January 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100108115828/http://www.goldenglobes.org/nominations/ |archivedate=January 8, 2010 |df= }}</ref>\n\nIn February 2012, LeBlanc appeared in the second episode of the eighteenth series of [[Top Gear (2002 TV series)|''Top Gear'']], where he set the fastest lap time in the \"[[Top Gear (2002 TV series)#Star in a car|Star in a Reasonably Priced Car]]\" segment in a [[Kia Cee'd]]. Lapping at 1:42.1, he beat the show's previous recordholder [[Rowan Atkinson]] by 0.1 seconds.<ref name=\"Episode 2\" /> He also appeared in the fourth episode of the nineteenth season to race the New Kia Cee'd, and beat his previous time.\n\nIn February 2016, the BBC announced LeBlanc had signed on to become one of the new ''Top Gear'' hosts,<ref>{{cite web |title=Matt LeBlanc joins Top Gear! |url=http://www.topgear.com/car-news/top-gear-tv/matt-leblanc-joins-top-gear |website=Top Gear |accessdate=February 4, 2016|date=February 4, 2016 }}</ref> signing a new two-year deal later that year.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-37470962 |title=Top Gear: Matt LeBlanc signs two-series deal |date=September 26, 2016 |website=BBC News |accessdate=August 22, 2017}}</ref> He announced his decision to retire from the series in May 2018, having co-hosted it for three years. Despite the show being \"great fun\", he stated the \"time commitment and extensive travel takes me away from my family and friends more than I'm comfortable with.\"<ref>{{cite news|title = Matt LeBlanc to leave Top Gear|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-44320696|website = BBC News|date = 2018-05-31|accessdate = 2019-04-07|df = mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nLeBlanc plays the lead role in the [[CBS]] sitcom ''[[Man with a Plan (TV series)|Man with a Plan]]'', which began airing in 2016.<ref name=\"CBS Fall Premiere Dates\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/06/cbs-fall-premiere-dates-2016-1201776569/ |title=CBS Sets Fall 2016 Premiere Dates, Slates JonBenet Ramsey Limited Series |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=June 21, 2016 |accessdate=June 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nLeBlanc married Melissa McKnight, a British-born American model, in May 2003.<ref name=people-divorce>{{cite magazine |last=Wulff |first=Jennifer |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20157263,00.html |title=Matt Leblanc's Surprise Split |magazine=People |volume=65 |number=15 |date=April 17, 2006 |accessdate=November 3, 2010}}</ref> They had been introduced in 1997 by McKnight's friend, wife of actor [[Lou Diamond Phillips]]. LeBlanc proposed to her a year later.<ref name=people-divorce /> Their daughter, born in 2004, began suffering seizures at eight months old. By the time she was two years old, the condition, thought to be a form of [[dysplasia]], had mostly subsided.<ref name=people-divorce /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/12143835/New-Top-Gear-presenter-Matt-LeBlanc-on-his-daughter-his-marriage-breakdown-and-his-darkest-years.html |first=Patrick |last=Sawer |date=February 6, 2016 |title=New Top Gear presenter Matt LeBlanc on his daughter, his marriage breakdown and his darkest years |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=August 22, 2017}}</ref> LeBlanc and McKnight divorced in October 2006, citing [[irreconcilable differences]].<ref name=people-otherwoman>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1180477,00.html |magazine=People |title=Matt LeBlanc's Other Woman |date=April 6, 2006 |accessdate=March 27, 2009}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year!!Title!!Role!!Notes\n|-\n|1987\n|''Doll Day Afternoon''\n|GI Joe\n|Film debut, short film\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Jon Bon Jovi|Jon Bon Jovi: Miracle]]''\n|Friend\n|rowspan=2|Music video, short video\n|-\n|1991\n|''[[Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers|Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers: Into the Great Wide Open]]''\n|Young man\n|-\n|1993\n|''Grey Knight''\n|Terhue\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Red Shoe Diaries|Red Shoe Diaries 3: Another Woman's Lipstick]]''\n|Kyle\n|Segment: \"Just Like That\"\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Lookin' Italian]]''\n|Anthony Manetti\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Friends]]\n|Joey Tribianni\n|Music video, video short\n|-\n|1996\n|''[[Ed (film)|Ed]]''\n|Jack 'Deuce\u2019 Cooper\n|friends forever \n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Red Shoe Diaries|Red Shoe Diaries 7: Burning Up]]''\n|Jed\n|Segment: \"Kidnap\"\n|-\n|1998\n|''[[Lost in Space (film)|Lost in Space]]''\n|Major Don West\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Jon Bon Jovi|Bon Jovi: Say It Isn't So]]''\n|Unknown\n|Music video, short video\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Charlie's Angels (2000 film)|Charlie's Angels]]''\n|Jason Gibbs\n|\n|-\n|2001\n|''[[All the Queen's Men]]''\n|O'Rourke\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|''[[Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle]]''